OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMP Paul Scully sorry for   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'no-go' areas comment      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, London Conservative MP and former      
OL,6, minister Paul Scully has apologised for
OL,7, suggesting there are "no-go" areas in  
OL,8, parts of Tower Hamlets.                
OL,10,FHe made the comment in radio and TV    
OL,11,Finterviews on Monday, prompting        
OL,12,Faccusations of Islamophobia and a      
OL,13,Frebuke from the prime minister.        
OL,15,FMr Scully had also said some people    
OL,16,Fwere "fearful for going out".          
OL,18,FIn a BBC Radio London interview on     
OL,19,FTuesday, he said he "put his hands up" 
OL,20,Ffor using language he "regrets".       
